comments.text:
LOL — Look Who’s Talking Now?

Exactly. Iran isn’t a football team. 
You don’t cheer for the destruction of a Muslim nation — any Muslim nation.

But let’s get real: Salafi, Wahhabi, Deobandi, and Ikhwani brainwashed zombies helped destroy Afghanistan in the 1980s — and much of the Muslim world cheered.
 Some still do.
Remember Rambo? 
That Hollywood fantasy wasn’t fiction — it was a metaphor.The West weaponized Muslims to fight their proxy wars. 
Afghanistan became the battlefield. And the Ummah went blind, thanks to the tools of Dajjal — Wahhabi ideology and the cursed legacy of Ibn Sa’ud.

Then came Libya. Syria. Yemen. Iraq. All burned using the same old blueprint — The one set in motion when the horns of Shaytan rose from Najd, just as our Prophet ﷺ warned.

T.E. Lawrence? Not a hero — a devil’s diplomat. He didn’t free the Arabs — he fractured them.
 The British Empire didn’t just invade — it injected poison into Islam, and outsourced Dajjal’s job to misguided Muslims.

Now we shout “Takfir!” Labeling brothers as kafir, Even long-dead leaders who can’t defend themselves, As if fake news and forged videos photoshop didn’t exist before 1948?

George Orwell’s ‘1984’ was no fiction. It was a warning — about British radio propaganda (BBC).
 The same propaganda that fed the Wahhabi coup in Afghanistan in 1929… And again in 1979… And again in Lebanon, Somalia, Syria — over and over.

Muslims keep killing each other in mindless takfiri blindness, While the enemies of Islam laugh… and profit.Iran. Pakistan. The Gulf. Morocco. 
They all played their roles. Coming on “holiday jihad” to Afghanistan, Killing the real mujahideen who resisted both colonialism and neocolonialism — Screaming Allahu Akbar, but really serving Uncle Sam.
Or more truthfully: Dollar Akbar.

It all started with Wahhabism — Which killed the Ottoman Caliphate, the last true Muslim empire —And cleared the path for Israel (1948) and its twin sister Pakistan (1947), both colonial experiments.

Same blueprint. Different names. Same destruction.

But here’s the divine irony:
Allah ﷻ is the Best of Planners.
Fifty NATO nations, the most powerful army in history,Were humiliated by barefoot Afghans.

And still — the world gives credit to everyone except Afghanistan. 
The media says Iran did it. Or Pakistan. Or some Arab puppet.

But never the Afghan people — The true Graveyard of Empires.

Even before NATO, it was the Persians, then the British, then West Pakistan — Invading, looting, and corrupting our Deen for over 300 years.

With “brothers” like these? Afghanistan needed no enemies. Even Shaytan went jobless.

This isn’t just geopolitics. This is Kifarah — divine consequence.
And yet… 
The Ummah still sleeps.
Too many Muslims still love “Rā‘inā”, When Allah clearly commanded:
“Do not say Rā‘inā, but say Unẓurnā, and listen…”— Surah Al-Baqarah 2:104

Astaghfirullah. Shame. Tawbah.
Even in 2025, when the truth is one click away — Nobody thinks
Nobody reflects. Nobody ponders. Nobody listens.

@kaidouz7756  You clearly missed my point. No one attacked Shaykh Asrar — I love him for the sake of Allah ﷻ, just as I do you and every believer.

But let’s be real: the Prophet ﷺ wasn’t Sunni or Shia. He followed the pure deen — built on akhlaq, adab, and the jihad of the nafs.

Today, we wave sectarian labels like team flags, while the soul of Islam — inner reform — is forgotten.

With 0% understanding of geopolitics, many are quick to judge, slander, and even justify the destruction of entire nations. Don’t pretend that’s not the reality for the majority.

Some even declare long-buried Muslim leaders kafir — often triggered by a sheikh himself — as if they know what only Allah ﷻ knows: the hearts and intentions of His servants.

All in the name of religion.
Astaghfirullah.

@MuslimSkeptic you are wrong s heikh look what ibnu taymiyah says 
Sheikh al-Islam Ibn Taymiyyah, may God have mercy on him, said:
"If the Magians, the Rafidis, and the Jews fight, then thank God for relieving the Muslims of their violence, and pray to God that your tribulation will not be due to one of them."
[Al-Fatawa al-Kubra 4/13]

This statement demonstrates a precise jurisprudence and a firm approach for the Sunnis. It is not rejoicing in bloodshed or tribulations, but rather rejoicing in the elimination of the evil of the sects that have long harmed Islam and its people.

 The Imam grouped the Magians, the Rafidis, and the Jews together because they share a shared, apparent or hidden, enmity toward Islam, and each has well-known stances in the history of the Ummah.
As for his statement, "And pray to God that your trial will not be due to one of them," it is a grave warning. Some people may think that one of the two parties is less important, and may fall into siding with it and be tempted by it, even though they are in fact among the people of misguidance.
This is a warning to Muslims to adhere to the community of Ahl al-Sunnah, not to be drawn into false conflicts, and not to support one deviant group over another simply out of enmity with a third party.
If the people of innovation or enemies of the religion fight, it is wise to thank God for repelling their evil, adhere to the roots of the Sunnis, and avoid all tribulations in which truth cannot be distinguished from falsehood.
We should not prioritize our personal interests over religion, nor should we substitute our firm faith for the stance of one of them, lest we be recorded before God among apostates and people of misguidance. God will gather us with the enemies of God and His Messenger, God forbid, and we will not know.
قال شيخ الإسلام ابن تيمية رحمه الله :
“إذا اقتتل المجوس والرافضة واليهود ، فاحمد الله أن أراح المسلمين من بأسهم ، وادع الله أن لا تكون فتنتك في أحدهما.”
[الفتاوى الكبرى ٤ / ١٣]
